	(866,2,'2014-11-07 15:55:04','2014-11-07 15:55:04','[quote]Soco stands for Southern Contemporary. It\'s a new and adventurous culinary approach to dishes that we have all come to know and love. At Soco we are focused on true Southern hospitality, and we are committed to overall excellence.[quote-citation][quote-author]Greg Richie[/quote-author] Executive Chef/Partner[/quote-citation][/quote]\n\n[divider][/divider][section-heading]Our Story[/section-heading][column-wrap][column size=\"one-half\"]\n\nExecutive Chef/Partner Greg Richie created his vision for Soco over many years of thought and experience. Ultimately, Soco Restaurant came to life. Located in the beautiful neighborhood of Thornton Park, the restaurant offers guests a truly unique and progressive culinary experience rooted in the vision of ideals developed by Chef Richie.\n\nAt Soco, we believe in the wholesomeness of food and the integrity of its preparation. Presented in an environment of true southern hospitality, Soco offers guests the tradition of time-honored classics, combined with the excitement of the contemporary. We are dedicated to the culinary renaissance of Downtown Orlando and strive to provide our guests with a delicious and memorable dining experience.\n\nThe restaurant was designed by <a href=\"http://www.thegravitycompany.com\">The Gravity Company</a>, who worked collaboratively with the owners to provide an urban and contemporary setting combined with classic southern elements.\n\nThe windows of Soco’s dining room and patio overlook the lively corner of Central Boulevard and Summerlin Avenue in the heart of Thornton Park. The grand window into our kitchen allowed guests to watch our culinary team prepare their carefully composed dishes, just as you would peek into your own kitchen and watch your favorite home-cooked meals being prepared. At the bar, neighbors and friends greet each other over a uniquely crafted cocktail or snifter of bourbon from our extensive whiskey list. Our semi-private room is the ideal downtown location for a business dinner, special event or group function.\n\n[section-heading]Our Group[/section-heading]\n\nSoco is owned and operated by the <a href=\"http://www.thorntonparkrg.com\">Thornton Park Restaurant Group</a>. We are proud to be a local and independent ownership group. Our sister restaurant is <a href=\"http://www.cityfishorlando.com\">Cityfish</a>, located a few doors down from Soco at 617 East Central Boulevard. TPRG is developing a new concept for the former Urban Rethink Bookstore space at 625 East Central Boulevard, next door to Soco. For more information, please click the logo below:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.thorntonparkrg.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-673\" style=\"width: 190px !important; height: 109px !important; margin-bottom: 0px !important;\" src=\"http://dev.socothorntonpark.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/TPRG-logo.png\" alt=\"TPRG-logo\" width=\"190\" height=\"109\" /></a>\n\n[section-heading]Our Friends[/section-heading]\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thorntonparkdistrict.com\" target=\"_blank\">Thornton Park District</a>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12px; display: block; position: relative; margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">- Our community</span></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thegravitycompany.com\" target=\"_blank\">The Gravity Company</a>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12px; display: block; position: relative; margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">- Our designers</span></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.sunshineplate.org\" target=\"_blank\">Sunshine Plate Coalition</a>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12px; display: block; position: relative; margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">- Greater Orlando food leaders alliance</span></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.southernfoodways.org\" target=\"_blank\">Southern Foodways Alliance</a>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12px; display: block; position: relative; margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">- Regional alliance celebrating the culinary diversity of the American South</span></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ustlercommunity.com\" target=\"_blank\">Ustler Group of Companies Community Involvement</a>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12px; display: block; position: relative; margin-top: -4px; margin-bottom: 5px;\">- Regional alliance celebrating the culinary diversity of the American South</span></li>\n</ul>\n[/column][column size=\"one-half aboutImg\"]<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-651 size-full\" src=\"http://dev.socothorntonpark.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/About-Content1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"490\" height=\"579\" />\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Our Other Brands</h2>\n<div class=\"cityfish-logo\"><a href=\"http://www.cityfishorlando.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-672\" style=\"width: 170px !important; height: 89px !important; margin-bottom: 0!important;\" src=\"http://dev.socothorntonpark.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/city-fish-logo.png\" alt=\"city-fish-logo\" width=\"170\" height=\"89\" /></a><span style=\"margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 14px; display: block;\">(click logo for more info)</span></div>\n<div class=\"cityfish-info\">\n\n<strong>Cityfish Restaurant</strong>\n617 E. Central Blvd.\nDowntown Orlando\n407-849-9779\n<a href=\"http://www.cityfishorlando.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.cityfishorlando.com</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n[/column][/column-wrap]','About','','inherit','open','open','','189-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 15:55:04','2014-11-07 15:55:04','',189,'http://www.socothorntonpark.com/189-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
